'''''Battle Group''''' is a 1986 [[computer wargame]] designed by [[Gary Grigsby]] and published by [[Strategic Simulations]]. It is a follow-up to Grigsby's earlier ''[[Kampfgruppe (video game)|Kampfgruppe]]''.

==Gameplay==
''Battle Group'' is a [[computer wargame]] that simulates the [[Western Front of World War II]] at the [[platoon]] scale, between 1943 and 1945. It features an [[Map editor|editor]] that allows players to create their own combat scenarios.<ref name=vgce>{{cite journal | author=Katz, Arnie | title=Waging World War II: Military Simulations for Computers and Video Games | date=February 1989 | journal=[[VideoGames & Computer Entertainment]] | pages=76–82 }}</ref>

==Development==
''Battle Group'' was designed by [[Gary Grigsby]] and published by [[Strategic Simulations|Strategic Simulations Inc.]] (SSI).<ref name=guru /> It is a follow-up to Grigsby's game ''[[Kampfgruppe (video game)|Kampfgruppe]]'',<ref name=computerplay /> and reuses that title's [[game engine]] and [[Game mechanics|mechanics]].<ref name="CGW29" /> ''Battle Group'' was released in 1986, the same year Grigsby and SSI launched ''[[Warship (video game)|Warship]]''.<ref name=guru>{{cite magazine | author=Emrich, Alan | title=The Pioneering Spirit of a Wargame Guru | date=September 1995 | issue=134 | magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] | pages=201, 202, 204 }}</ref>

==Reception==
